  "title": "Add Number & Date Dictation listening drill",
  "description": "Create a new focused listening micro-drill 'Number Dictation' that helps users decode commonly-misheard spoken numerics (large numbers like 'fifteen vs fifty', prices '$3.49', years '2019', dates 'March 3rd', times '7:45', phone numbers). This targets a real pain point for ESL learners and complements existing listening drills without duplicating any recent additions.\n\nBackend (app/routers/number_dictation.py):\n- POST /api/number-dictation/start: takes optional category ('teens_vs_tens', 'prices', 'dates', 'times', 'years', 'mixed') and difficulty; returns a session with N=6 items. Each item has: id, category, expected_text (e.g. '7:45 PM'), spoken_form (e.g. 'quarter to eight in the evening' OR 'seven forty-five PM'), audio_url generated via existing TTS (reuse the TTS helper used in app/routers/listening.py or shadowing.py — inspect to reuse). Items should be deterministically generated in Python (no LLM call needed) using a small templated generator inside the router module so the drill is fast/cheap.\n- POST /api/number-dictation/answer: body {item_id, user_answer}; normalizes both expected and user input (strip $, commas, lowercase, collapse whitespace, accept '7:45' == '745' == '7 45') and returns {correct: bool, expected_normalized, user_normalized, hint}.\n- POST /api/number-dictation/complete: body {session_id, results[]}; persists a summary row.\n\nDatabase (app/database.py): add table number_dictation_sessions(id INTEGER PK, created_at TEXT, category TEXT, total INTEGER, correct INTEGER, accuracy REAL). Add migration to _MIGRATIONS:\n  \"CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS number_dictation_sessions (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT, created_at TEXT NOT NULL, category TEXT, total INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0, correct INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0, accuracy REAL NOT NULL DEFAULT 0)\"\n(No ALTER needed since this is a brand-new table.) Register the router in app/main.py.\n\nFrontend (frontend/src/pages/NumberDictation.tsx + route entry in frontend/src/App.tsx and a home card link): UI flow:\n1. Category picker (chips: Teens vs Tens, Prices, Dates, Times, Years, Mixed) with a Start button.\n2. Per-item card: large 🔊 Play button (autoplay first time), Replay button (counts replays), text input field, Submit. After submit show ✅/❌ with expected vs heard, plus a small 'Tip' line (e.g. 'Listen for stress: FIFteen vs fifTEEN').\n3. Progress bar (item k/6) and final results screen showing accuracy %, category breakdown, and a 'Practice missed again' button that restarts only the wrong items.\n\nKeep scope tight: single new router file, single new page, one new DB table, plus main.py + App.tsx wiring + a small home-page entry card.",
